## JSON Schema Law
The frontend expects this EXACT shape from `/api/analyze`. Never change field names:
```json
{
  "ticker": "TSLA",
  "asset_price": 185.20,
  "asset_change_pct": 2.4,
  "volatility_30d": 38.4,
  "memo": {
    "bull_verdict": "...",
    "bear_verdict": "...",
    "summary": "...",
    "price_target": 220.00,
    "rating": "BULLISH"
  },
  "thesis_points": [
    {"id": 1, "text": "...", "status": "PASS", "current_value": "19.2%"}
  ],
  "agent_logs": [
    {"agent": "FUNDAMENTAL", "message": "...", "ts": 0.2}
  ]
}
```

## Cerebras Call Pattern
```python
from cerebras.cloud.sdk import Cerebras
import os, json

client = Cerebras(api_key=os.environ["CEREBRAS_API_KEY"])

def call_agent(system_prompt: str, user_message: str) -> dict:
    response = client.chat.completions.create(
        model="gemma2-31b-it",
        messages=[
            {"role": "system", "content": system_prompt},
            {"role": "user", "content": user_message}
        ],
        response_format={"type": "json_object"},
        max_tokens=1500,
        temperature=0.3,
    )
    return json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content)
```

